2026-04-16 14:54:43 [INFO] Tool invocation completed. Tool: send_email, Arguments: {"content_message":"Subject: How to set low‑battery (15%) and low‑range (80 km) alerts in most EV apps\n\nHello,\n\nHere’s a generic, step‑by‑step guide you can follow in most EV mobile apps on iOS and Android to set:\n- a low‑battery alert at 15% state of charge, and\n- a low‑range alert at 80 km (or the nearest option the app provides).\n\nStep 1: Prep\n- Make sure your vehicle is linked to the app, you’re signed in, and the car has connectivity.\n- Update the app to the latest version.\n\nStep 2: Enable push notifications on your phone\n- iOS: Open Settings > Notifications > your EV app > Allow Notifications. Enable Alerts, Sounds, and Badges.\n- Android: Open Settings > Apps > your EV app > Notifications > Allow. Also set Battery to Unrestricted (Settings > Apps > your EV app > Battery > Unrestricted) so alerts aren’t delayed.\n\nStep 3: Open in‑app notification settings\n- In the EV app, go to Profile or Settings.\n- Find Notifications, Alerts, or Vehicle Alerts.\n\nStep 4: Set the low‑battery alert to 15%\n- In the Battery or Charging alerts section, choose Low battery threshold.\n- Set it to 15% SOC and save.\n\nStep 5: Set the low‑range alert to 80 km (or nearest)\n- In the Range or Distance alerts section, choose Low range threshold.\n- If 80 km is available, select 80 km. If not, pick the nearest available option and note what you chose.\n- Save.\n\nStep 6: Optional reliability tips\n- Enable background refresh: iOS Settings > General > Background App Refresh. On Android, allow background data for the EV app.\n- If recommended by the app, allow Location access (While Using or Always) to support connectivity features.\n- In the car’s infotainment, make sure data sharing/connectivity options are enabled.\n\nStep 7: Test the alerts\n- After saving, take a short drive or adjust the thresholds temporarily to trigger a test alert, then set them back to your desired values.\n\nIf you need model‑specific steps later, reply with your EV make/model and app name.\n\nBest regards","email_addresses":["alex.kim@example.com"]}
