For charging before departure in Madrid, I found a great fast charger nearby: Repsol with a 350 kW DC plug and it’s available 24/7. A quick top‑up from 70% to 90% would take about 4 minutes. Along the route, a good mid‑trip stop is Ionity around the 400 km mark with 300 kW DC available; stopping there to go from roughly 25–40% up to 80% should take about 8–11 minutes, with about a 7‑minute detour. If you want a second short splash, there’s Freshmile around the 800 km mark with a 200 kW DC plug available; figure about a 10‑minute charge and a 5‑minute detour. Factoring quick charging and brief detours, your ETA is more like 00:35–00:45. I can keep it conservative in the email so expectations are clear.

